        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 8:20PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 819 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Eckley, or 13 miles northwest of Wray, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern Yuma
County.

This includes Highway 385 between mile markers 252 and 257.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
